    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>These spirits, the incorporeal manifestations of two mythical lions called Ming and Miang, dwell within an ancient vase known as Shishi. The pair act as guardian spirits and consider it their sacred duty to protect both the vase and its bearer—a responsibility they take very seriously. While inside Shishi, a depiction of Ming and Miang standing sentry at the entrance to a picturesque temple can be seen painted on it, their snarling visage clearly indicating that they're just waiting to be unleashed.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong style=\"color:#191813\">Rule Clarification, Shishi.</strong><span style=\"color:#191813\"> Full rules for the guardian lion can be found in  @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.85LJV9qO0jokrQMq]{Shishi}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "public": ""
